parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Pump Failure and Fuel Leak
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump can cause a fuel leak, which can lead to a fire hazard, especially in hot weather conditions. This can result in serious injury or death.
symptoms: fuel leak from the top of the fuel tank
fuel dripping down the side of the tank

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent surging and lurching of the vehicle can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: Intermittent surging or lurching of the vehicle at low speeds
especially when starting from a stop

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the electrical system can cause loss of power, stalling, and sudden deceleration, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: and failure of various electrical components such as headlights

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: ETM failure can cause sudden loss of power, stalling, and reduced engine performance, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: and failure of the throttle control module.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Clutch and transmission problems can cause loss of control, stalling, and sudden deceleration, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
clutch pedal sticks to the floor
and grinding or clunking noises when shifting gears.
